SENATE RESOLUTION 333
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Ellie L. Thompson on
the celebration of her 100th birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to those citizens who are celebrating
special occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, Ellie L. Thompson will celebrate her 100th birthday on April 12, 2026, a
milestone commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant; and
WHEREAS, born on April 12, 1926, in Campobello, South Carolina, Mrs. Thompson is
the proud mother of three children, Delores Ann, Barbara, and Matthew, Jr., two of whom are
deceased; grandmother of seven, two of whom are deceased; great-grandmother of sixteen;
and great-great-grandmother of eleven; and
WHEREAS, wholly devoted to her family, she has enjoyed the love and companionship
of her children; throughout her life, Ellie Thompson cared for and supported her son Matthew,
Jr., during his illness, and her daughter, Delores Ann, during her decline in health, until they
departed from this earthly life; and
WHEREAS, as Mrs. Thompson gracefully enters her 100th year, she remains a positive
force for good, devoted to family values of the highest order, and cherishes the bonds she has
with her family; and
WHEREAS, she is a devout member of Greater St. John Baptist Church and regularly
attended Sunday School and Bible study until she was no longer able to do so; she served her
church as president of the Mothers Ministry, president of the Willing Workers, and Sunday
School class superintendent; and
SR0333
014267
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ellie Thompson now spends her golden years holding down the end of her
sofa and rocking in her chair on the front porch; she continues to read her Bible, complete word
searches, watch old westerns and shows, and keep up with the daily news; and
WHEREAS, we wish to grasp this golden opportunity to specially recognize Mrs.
Thompson on this very special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby honor and
congratulate Ellie L. Thompson on the celebration of her 100th birthday and extend to her our
best wishes for many happy returns of the day.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
